In Indian languages, prahar is a unit of time. A day is divided into eight Prahars, making each prahar equivalent to three hours. The first prahar starts at 3am.

In Hindustani Music there are ragas which are prescribed to be performed at particular prahar to maximize their aesthetic effects.

1st Prahar (3 AM to 6 AM)
2nd Prahar (6 AM to 9 AM)
3rd Prahar (9 AM to 12 PM)
4th Prahar (12 PM to 3 PM)
5th Prahar (3 PM to 6 PM)
6th Prahar (6 PM to 9 PM)
7th Prahar (9 PM to 12 AM)
8th Prahar (12 AM to 3 AM)